						<summary>

						<p>This is the same as Kulōttuṅga I. The inscription begins with a short introduction <hi rend="bold">Bhūmiyum-tiruvum</hi> etc. It registers an assignment of land (under the orders of the king) by <hi rend="italic">sēnāpati</hi> Rājēndraśōḻa-Brahmādhirāja and the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Kuṅgaṉūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vaḷavanārāyaṇachaturvēdimaṅgalam in Puli-nāḍu, a division of Raṭṭapāḍikoṇḍaśōḻamaṇḍalam for the construction of a tank called the Rājēndraśōḻapperiyēri in the village.</p>						

						</summary>
